        <summary>What is Acrew Capital?</summary>
        <p>Acrew Capital is a multi-stage venture capital firm that invests in transformative technology companies across sectors like financial services, cyber security, data infrastructure, and community-driven platforms.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What companies are in the Acrew Capital portfolio?</summary>
        <p>The Acrew Capital portfolio includes well-known tech and fintech companies such as Chime, Gusto, Discord, Plaid, and CoinTracker, among many other early- and growth-stage startups.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How does Acrew Capital choose its investments?</summary>
        <p>Acrew focuses on thesis-driven investing. They identify macro trends—such as the decentralization of finance or the rise of Web3—and back diverse, visionary founders building foundational infrastructure in those sectors.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can individual investors buy into the Acrew Capital portfolio?</summary>
        <p>Generally, no. Acrew Capital is a private venture capital firm, meaning their funds are typically only accessible to institutional investors and accredited high-net-worth individuals. However, retail investors can buy shares if a portfolio company eventually goes public.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the difference between a venture capital firm and a private equity firm?</summary>
        <p>Venture capital (VC) firms like Acrew invest in early-stage, high-growth startups in exchange for equity, taking on high risk for massive potential returns. Private equity (PE) firms typically buy mature, established companies, often taking them private to restructure and increase efficiency.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
